This paper discusses techniques for hiding parts of an ontology, which is a fundamental concept in artificial intelligence and knowledge representation. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves querying and reasoning over ontologies, which are topics related to databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the import by query approach, which is a software engineering technique (cs.SE) and involves natural language processing (cs.CL).
